{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1056,"text":"On the path that American children \ntravel to adulthood,"},{"time":4971,"text":"two institutions oversee the journey."},{"time":8519,"text":"The first is the one we hear \na lot about: college."},{"time":12262,"text":"Some of you may remember\nthe excitement that you felt"},{"time":14845,"text":"when you first set off for college."},{"time":17431,"text":"Some of you may be in college right now"},{"time":19983,"text":"and you're feeling this excitement\nat this very moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23988,"text":"College has some shortcomings."},{"time":25667,"text":"It's expensive; it leaves\nyoung people in debt."},{"time":29003,"text":"But all in all, it's a pretty good path."},{"time":31947,"text":"Young people emerge from college\nwith pride and with great friends"},{"time":37114,"text":"and with a lot of knowledge \nabout the world."},{"time":39453,"text":"And perhaps most importantly,"},{"time":41289,"text":"a better chance in the labor market\nthan they had before they got there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45795,"text":"Today I want to talk about\nthe second institution"},{"time":48498,"text":"overseeing the journey from childhood\nto adulthood in the United States."},{"time":54056,"text":"And that institution is prison."},{"time":58791,"text":"Young people on this journey\nare meeting with probation officers"},{"time":62536,"text":"instead of with teachers."},{"time":64939,"text":"They're going to court dates\ninstead of to class."},{"time":68832,"text":"Their junior year abroad is instead\na trip to a state correctional facility."},{"time":73909,"text":"And they're emerging from their 20s"},{"time":76599,"text":"not with degrees in business and English,"},{"time":79796,"text":"but with criminal records."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82514,"text":"This institution is also costing us a lot,"},{"time":85107,"text":"about 40,000 dollars a year"},{"time":86749,"text":"to send a young person\nto prison in New Jersey."},{"time":91167,"text":"But here, taxpayers are footing the bill"},{"time":93723,"text":"and what kids are getting\nis a cold prison cell"},{"time":97206,"text":"and a permanent mark against them\nwhen they come home"},{"time":100016,"text":"and apply for work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102765,"text":"There are more and more kids\non this journey to adulthood"},{"time":106211,"text":"than ever before in the United States\nand that's because in the past 40 years,"},{"time":111435,"text":"our incarceration rate \nhas grown by 700 percent."},{"time":117187,"text":"I have one slide for this talk."},{"time":119316,"text":"Here it is."},{"time":121760,"text":"Here's our incarceration rate,"},{"time":123623,"text":"about 716 people per 100,000\nin the population."},{"time":131205,"text":"Here's the OECD countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138885,"text":"What's more, it's poor kids\nthat we're sending to prison,"},{"time":141617,"text":"too many drawn from African-American\nand Latino communities"},{"time":145105,"text":"so that prison now stands firmly between\nthe young people trying to make it"},{"time":149986,"text":"and the fulfillment of the American Dream."},{"time":153418,"text":"The problem's actually \na bit worse than this"},{"time":156274,"text":"'cause we're not just sending \npoor kids to prison,"},{"time":158952,"text":"we're saddling poor kids with court fees,"},{"time":161919,"text":"with probation and parole restrictions,"},{"time":164240,"text":"with low-level warrants,"},{"time":166127,"text":"we're asking them to live \nin halfway houses and on house arrest,"},{"time":169622,"text":"and we're asking them \nto negotiate a police force"},{"time":173227,"text":"that is entering poor\ncommunities of color,"},{"time":175640,"text":"not for the purposes \nof promoting public safety,"},{"time":178839,"text":"but to make arrest counts,\nto line city coffers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186537,"text":"This is the hidden underside to our\nhistoric experiment in punishment:"},{"time":190925,"text":"young people worried that at any moment,\nthey will be stopped, searched and seized."},{"time":196635,"text":"Not just in the streets, \nbut in their homes,"},{"time":199258,"text":"at school and at work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202925,"text":"I got interested in this \nother path to adulthood"},{"time":206116,"text":"when I was myself a college student"},{"time":208357,"text":"attending the University of Pennsylvania"},{"time":210415,"text":"in the early 2000s."},{"time":212493,"text":"Penn sits within a historic \nAfrican-American neighborhood."},{"time":216060,"text":"So you've got these two parallel\njourneys going on simultaneously:"},{"time":221298,"text":"the kids attending \nthis elite, private university,"},{"time":224419,"text":"and the kids from \nthe adjacent neighborhood,"},{"time":226885,"text":"some of whom are making it to college,"},{"time":228813,"text":"and many of whom \nare being shipped to prison."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232831,"text":"In my sophomore year, I started tutoring\na young woman who was in high school"},{"time":237415,"text":"who lived about 10 minutes\naway from the university."},{"time":240409,"text":"Soon, her cousin came home \nfrom a juvenile detention center."},{"time":243942,"text":"He was 15, a freshman in high school."},{"time":246600,"text":"I began to get to know him \nand his friends and family,"},{"time":250259,"text":"and I asked him what he thought \nabout me writing about his life"},{"time":253611,"text":"for my senior thesis in college."},{"time":256196,"text":"This senior thesis became\na dissertation at Princeton"},{"time":260387,"text":"and now a book."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261935,"text":"By the end of my sophomore year,"},{"time":263533,"text":"I moved into the neighborhood\nand I spent the next six years"}]},{"cues":[{"time":266903,"text":"trying to understand what young people\nwere facing as they came of age."},{"time":272234,"text":"The first week I spent\nin this neighborhood,"},{"time":274318,"text":"I saw two boys, five and seven years old,"},{"time":276894,"text":"play this game of chase,"},{"time":278386,"text":"where the older boy\nran after the other boy."},{"time":281337,"text":"He played the cop."},{"time":282532,"text":"When the cop caught up\nto the younger boy,"},{"time":284720,"text":"he pushed him down,"},{"time":286420,"text":"handcuffed him with imaginary handcuffs,"},{"time":288971,"text":"took a quarter out of \nthe other child's pocket,"},{"time":291282,"text":"saying, \"I'm seizing that.\""},{"time":294874,"text":"He asked the child if \nhe was carrying any drugs"},{"time":298214,"text":"or if he had a warrant."},{"time":300659,"text":"Many times, I saw this game repeated,"},{"time":302664,"text":"sometimes children would \nsimply give up running,"},{"time":305052,"text":"and stick their bodies flat \nagainst the ground"},{"time":307248,"text":"with their hands above their heads,\nor flat up against a wall."},{"time":310593,"text":"Children would yell at each other,"},{"time":312588,"text":"\"I'm going to lock you up,"},{"time":313870,"text":"I'm going to lock you up\nand you're never coming home!\""},{"time":317052,"text":"Once I saw a six-year-old child\npull another child's pants down"},{"time":321406,"text":"and try to do a cavity search."}]},{"cues":[{"time":324756,"text":"In the first 18 months that I lived\nin this neighborhood,"},{"time":327935,"text":"I wrote down every time I saw\nany contact between police"},{"time":331627,"text":"and people that were my neighbors."},{"time":334553,"text":"So in the first 18 months,"},{"time":336652,"text":"I watched the police stop \npedestrians or people in cars,"},{"time":340421,"text":"search people, run people's names,"},{"time":342589,"text":"chase people through the streets,"},{"time":344533,"text":"pull people in for questioning,"},{"time":346306,"text":"or make an arrest every single day,\nwith five exceptions."},{"time":351142,"text":"Fifty-two times, I watched the police\nbreak down doors,"},{"time":355077,"text":"chase people through houses"},{"time":357118,"text":"or make an arrest of someone\nin their home."},{"time":360337,"text":"Fourteen times\nin this first year and a half,"},{"time":363150,"text":"I watched the police punch, choke,\nkick, stomp on or beat young men"},{"time":368450,"text":"after they had caught them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372289,"text":"Bit by bit, I got to know two brothers,"},{"time":374665,"text":"Chuck and Tim."},{"time":376209,"text":"Chuck was 18 when we met,\na senior in high school."},{"time":379250,"text":"He was playing on the basketball team\nand making C's and B's."},{"time":382798,"text":"His younger brother, Tim, was 10."},{"time":384697,"text":"And Tim loved Chuck;\nhe followed him around a lot,"},{"time":387848,"text":"looked to Chuck to be a mentor."},{"time":390139,"text":"They lived with their mom and grandfather"},{"time":392285,"text":"in a two-story row home \nwith a front lawn and a back porch."},{"time":395724,"text":"Their mom was struggling with addiction\nall while the boys were growing up."},{"time":399385,"text":"She never really was able \nto hold down a job for very long."},{"time":403242,"text":"It was their grandfather's pension\nthat supported the family,"},{"time":406281,"text":"not really enough to pay\nfor food and clothes"},{"time":409484,"text":"and school supplies for growing boys."},{"time":412215,"text":"The family was really struggling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414401,"text":"So when we met, Chuck was\na senior in high school."},{"time":416780,"text":"He had just turned 18."},{"time":419628,"text":"That winter, a kid in the schoolyard"},{"time":422770,"text":"called Chuck's mom a crack whore."},{"time":426029,"text":"Chuck pushed the kid's face into the snow"},{"time":428904,"text":"and the school cops charged him \nwith aggravated assault."},{"time":432729,"text":"The other kid was fine the next day,"},{"time":434479,"text":"I think it was his pride that was injured\nmore than anything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437952,"text":"But anyway, since Chuck was 18,"},{"time":439665,"text":"this agg. assault case sent him \nto adult county jail"},{"time":442853,"text":"on State Road in northeast Philadelphia,"},{"time":445278,"text":"where he sat, unable to pay the bail --\nhe couldn't afford it --"},{"time":449345,"text":"while the trial dates \ndragged on and on and on"},{"time":452544,"text":"through almost his entire senior year."},{"time":455926,"text":"Finally, near the end of this season,"},{"time":458976,"text":"the judge on this assault case\nthrew out most of the charges"},{"time":462323,"text":"and Chuck came home"},{"time":463657,"text":"with only a few hundred dollars' worth\nof court fees hanging over his head."},{"time":468004,"text":"Tim was pretty happy that day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470547,"text":"The next fall, Chuck tried \nto re-enroll as a senior,"},{"time":473301,"text":"but the school secretary told him that"},{"time":475315,"text":"he was then 19 and too old \nto be readmitted."},{"time":478446,"text":"Then the judge on his assault case\nissued him a warrant for his arrest"},{"time":482113,"text":"because he couldn't pay \nthe 225 dollars in court fees"},{"time":485388,"text":"that came due a few weeks after\nthe case ended."},{"time":488915,"text":"Then he was a high school dropout\nliving on the run."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492935,"text":"Tim's first arrest came later that year"},{"time":494987,"text":"after he turned 11."},{"time":496770,"text":"Chuck had managed\nto get his warrant lifted"},{"time":498900,"text":"and he was on a payment plan\nfor the court fees"},{"time":501561,"text":"and he was driving Tim to school\nin his girlfriend's car."},{"time":505071,"text":"So a cop pulls them over, runs the car,"},{"time":507806,"text":"and the car comes up \nas stolen in California."},{"time":511591,"text":"Chuck had no idea where in the history\nof this car it had been stolen."},{"time":515714,"text":"His girlfriend's uncle bought it\nfrom a used car auction"},{"time":519190,"text":"in northeast Philly."},{"time":520657,"text":"Chuck and Tim had never been\noutside of the tri-state,"},{"time":523485,"text":"let alone to California."},{"time":525834,"text":"But anyway, the cops down at the precinct"},{"time":527932,"text":"charged Chuck with \nreceiving stolen property."},{"time":531500,"text":"And then a juvenile judge, \na few days later,"},{"time":534312,"text":"charged Tim, age 11,"},{"time":536464,"text":"with accessory to receiving\na stolen property"},{"time":539537,"text":"and then he was placed on \nthree years of probation."},{"time":544430,"text":"With this probation sentence \nhanging over his head,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":547332,"text":"Chuck sat his little brother down"},{"time":549419,"text":"and began teaching him\nhow to run from the police."},{"time":552868,"text":"They would sit side by side \non their back porch"},{"time":555200,"text":"looking out into the shared alleyway"},{"time":557264,"text":"and Chuck would coach Tim\nhow to spot undercover cars,"},{"time":561104,"text":"how to negotiate a late-night police raid,\nhow and where to hide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567011,"text":"I want you to imagine for a second"},{"time":568691,"text":"what Chuck and Tim's lives would be like"},{"time":571060,"text":"if they were living in a neighborhood\nwhere kids were going to college,"},{"time":575809,"text":"not prison."},{"time":577918,"text":"A neighborhood like the one \nI got to grow up in."},{"time":581071,"text":"Okay, you might say."},{"time":582536,"text":"But Chuck and Tim, kids like them,\nthey're committing crimes!"},{"time":586288,"text":"Don't they deserve to be in prison?"},{"time":588414,"text":"Don't they deserve to be \nliving in fear of arrest?"},{"time":592228,"text":"Well, my answer would be no."},{"time":595350,"text":"They don't."},{"time":596430,"text":"And certainly not for the same things \nthat other young people"},{"time":599457,"text":"with more privilege are doing\nwith impunity."},{"time":602901,"text":"If Chuck had gone to my high school,"},{"time":604718,"text":"that schoolyard fight \nwould have ended there,"},{"time":607041,"text":"as a schoolyard fight."},{"time":608717,"text":"It never would have become\nan aggravated assault case."},{"time":612937,"text":"Not a single kid that\nI went to college with"},{"time":615758,"text":"has a criminal record right now."},{"time":617437,"text":"Not a single one."},{"time":619311,"text":"But can you imagine how many might have\nif the police had stopped those kids"},{"time":623316,"text":"and searched their pockets for drugs\nas they walked to class?"},{"time":627183,"text":"Or had raided their frat parties\nin the middle of the night?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":632384,"text":"Okay, you might say."},{"time":633656,"text":"But doesn't this high incarceration rate"},{"time":635646,"text":"partly account for our \nreally low crime rate?"},{"time":638399,"text":"Crime is down. That's a good thing."},{"time":640823,"text":"Totally, that is a good thing.\nCrime is down."},{"time":643310,"text":"It dropped precipitously in\nthe '90s and through the 2000s."},{"time":646837,"text":"But according to a committee of academics"},{"time":648882,"text":"convened by the National Academy\nof Sciences last year,"},{"time":652536,"text":"the relationship between our\nhistorically high incarceration rates"},{"time":656545,"text":"and our low crime rate is pretty shaky."},{"time":660129,"text":"It turns out that the crime rate\ngoes up and down"},{"time":663569,"text":"irrespective of how many young people\nwe send to prison."}]},{"cues":[{"time":669265,"text":"We tend to think about justice\nin a pretty narrow way:"},{"time":672358,"text":"good and bad, innocent and guilty."},{"time":675962,"text":"Injustice is about being \nwrongfully convicted."},{"time":679317,"text":"So if you're convicted \nof something you did do,"},{"time":681632,"text":"you should be punished for it."},{"time":683467,"text":"There are innocent and guilty people,"},{"time":685233,"text":"there are victims and \nthere are perpetrators."},{"time":687670,"text":"Maybe we could think a little bit\nmore broadly than that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692071,"text":"Right now, we're asking kids who live\nin the most disadvantaged neighborhoods,"},{"time":696505,"text":"who have the least amount\nof family resources,"},{"time":698786,"text":"who are attending \nthe country's worst schools,"},{"time":701347,"text":"who are facing the toughest time\nin the labor market,"},{"time":704253,"text":"who are living in neighborhoods\nwhere violence is an everyday problem,"},{"time":707906,"text":"we're asking these kids to walk\nthe thinnest possible line --"},{"time":712479,"text":"to basically never do anything wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":716290,"text":"Why are we not providing support\nto young kids facing these challenges?"},{"time":720791,"text":"Why are we offering only handcuffs,\njail time and this fugitive existence?"},{"time":728037,"text":"Can we imagine something better?\n"},{"time":730543,"text":"Can we imagine a criminal justice system\nthat prioritizes recovery,"},{"time":734798,"text":"prevention, civic inclusion,"},{"time":737385,"text":"rather than punishment?"},{"time":740086,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":747855,"text":"A criminal justice system \nthat acknowledges"},{"time":750130,"text":"the legacy of exclusion that poor people\nof color in the U.S. have faced"},{"time":754110,"text":"and that does not promote\nand perpetuate those exclusions."},{"time":758266,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":763291,"text":"And finally, a criminal justice system\nthat believes in black young people,"},{"time":767853,"text":"rather than treating black young people \nas the enemy to be rounded up."},{"time":771717,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":779460,"text":"The good news is that we already are."},{"time":782287,"text":"A few years ago, Michelle Alexander\nwrote \"The New Jim Crow,\""},{"time":787110,"text":"which got Americans to see \nincarceration as a civil rights issue"},{"time":791123,"text":"of historic proportions in a way\nthey had not seen it before."},{"time":795479,"text":"President Obama and Attorney General \nEric Holder have come out very strongly"},{"time":799238,"text":"on sentencing reform,"},{"time":800955,"text":"on the need to address \nracial disparity in incarceration."},{"time":804699,"text":"We're seeing states throw out\nStop and Frisk"},{"time":807309,"text":"as the civil rights violation that it is."},{"time":810345,"text":"We're seeing cities and states\ndecriminalize possession of marijuana."},{"time":815400,"text":"New York, New Jersey\nand California"},{"time":817257,"text":"have been dropping their \nprison populations, closing prisons,"},{"time":821094,"text":"while also seeing a big drop in crime."},{"time":823375,"text":"Texas has gotten into the game now,"},{"time":825068,"text":"also closing prisons, \ninvesting in education."},{"time":828913,"text":"This curious coalition is building \nfrom the right and the left,"},{"time":832570,"text":"made up of former prisoners\nand fiscal conservatives,"},{"time":836018,"text":"of civil rights activists\nand libertarians,"},{"time":839349,"text":"of young people taking to the streets\nto protest police violence"},{"time":843329,"text":"against unarmed black teenagers,"},{"time":846165,"text":"and older, wealthier people --"},{"time":848211,"text":"some of you are here in the audience --"},{"time":850082,"text":"pumping big money into \ndecarceration initiatives"},{"time":855357,"text":"In a deeply divided Congress,"},{"time":857107,"text":"the work of reforming \nour criminal justice system"},{"time":859810,"text":"is just about the only thing\nthat the right and the left"},{"time":862602,"text":"are coming together on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":865187,"text":"I did not think I would see\nthis political moment in my lifetime."},{"time":869102,"text":"I think many of the people\nwho have been working tirelessly"},{"time":872710,"text":"to write about the causes and consequences"},{"time":874872,"text":"of our historically \nhigh incarceration rates"},{"time":877104,"text":"did not think we would see\nthis moment in our lifetime."},{"time":880870,"text":"The question for us now is,\nhow much can we make of it?"},{"time":884653,"text":"How much can we change?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":887618,"text":"I want to end with a call to young people,"},{"time":890182,"text":"the young people attending college"},{"time":891816,"text":"and the young people\nstruggling to stay out of prison"},{"time":894926,"text":"or to make it through prison\nand return home."},{"time":898030,"text":"It may seem like these paths\nto adulthood are worlds apart,"},{"time":902063,"text":"but the young people participating\nin these two institutions"},{"time":906505,"text":"conveying us to adulthood,"},{"time":908430,"text":"they have one thing in common:"},{"time":910995,"text":"Both can be leaders in the work\nof reforming our criminal justice system."},{"time":916483,"text":"Young people have always been leaders\nin the fight for equal rights,"},{"time":919815,"text":"the fight for more people \nto be granted dignity"},{"time":922080,"text":"and a fighting chance at freedom."},{"time":924635,"text":"The mission for the generation \nof young people"},{"time":927014,"text":"coming of age in this, a sea-change\nmoment, potentially,"},{"time":931994,"text":"is to end mass incarceration and \nbuild a new criminal justice system,"},{"time":937258,"text":"emphasis on the word justice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":940185,"text":"Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":941589,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}